      "side": 1,
      "message": "i\u0027m not aware of a doc, but roughly: more QPS \u003d\u003e more RAM + CPU.\nSo, watch for exhaustion of either:\n * RAM: detection: OOMs in logs, constant creation churn of new instances.\n   potential red herring: if code is leaky (e.g. goroutines, or LRU cache with too big N), more QPS will cause more frequent OOMs, but root cause are leaks, not QPS.\n\n * CPU: watch for either 100% CPU utilization (easy to spot) or sometimes spikes in latency despite low utilization -- this can be due to random long pauses due to CPU intensive works (e.g. submit order computation 😊)\n\n\nMy thinking here is that we should start with maximum possible QPS / instance (80 in GAE) and then adjust as needed.",
      "parentUuid": "c14f05f9_82a94d68",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 5,
